  "instructions": [
    "Rinse shrimp and pat dry, then sear in a non‑stick pan over medium heat for 2 minutes per side until pink; remove and set aside.",
    "In the same pan, add sesame oil, then sauté minced garlic and grated ginger until fragrant, about 30 seconds.",
    "Add shredded carrots and napa cabbage, cooking until just softened, about 3 minutes.",
    "Stir in the cooked rice, soy sauce, rice vinegar, and lime juice, mixing until the grains are well coated and heated through, about 2 minutes.",
    "Gently fold in the cooked shrimp and serrano ham slices, allowing the ham to warm and release its flavors without cooking further.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a bowl, top with scallion slices and toasted sesame seeds, then serve immediately."
